From: ask2 PR14z19 <ask2@local>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 05:46:00 +0000
Subject: fman_pcd: add pre-netdev hook + fman_port invoker (Path A)

PR14z19 Path A architectural pivot. Replaces the post-probe KG-graft
strategy (patches 0042 / 0043, archived) with a pre-netdev hook that
intercepts fman_port_init() BEFORE the default keygen_port_hashing_init()
call runs, so ASK2 can install its CC tree + KG scheme in place of the
mainline RSS scheme rather than mutating a live one.

Surface
-------
Public ABI (include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h):
  typedef int (*fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t)(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
              u8 hwport_id, u32 default_base_fqid,
              u32 default_hash_size, void *priv);
  int  fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
              fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t hook, void *priv);
  void fman_pcd_unregister_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd);

Both register/unregister are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL so a built-in ask.ko
fs_initcall can attach during fman_probe() but BEFORE dpaa_eth_probe().

Internal helper (fman_pcd_internal.h, same-module):
  int  fman_pcd_invoke_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
              u8 hwport_id, u32 default_base_fqid,
              u32 default_hash_size);

Hook return-code semantics
--------------------------
   0      -> hook claims this port; caller skips default RSS init.
  -ENOENT -> no hook registered for this port; caller falls through to
             mainline keygen_port_hashing_init().
  other negative -> fatal probe failure.

fman_port_init() integration
----------------------------
The pcd_fqs_count != 0 branch now queries the hook first, then either
short-circuits to fman_port_use_kg_hash(port, true) or falls through to
mainline. No behavior change when no hook is registered.

Locking
-------
Single hook slot per FMan instance, protected by pcd->lock during
install/uninstall. The hook itself is invoked OUTSIDE the lock so it
may sleep, allocate, and call back into PCD APIs.

